article.headline: Boise St. 64, Texas-Arlington 46
article.story: ARLINGTON, Texas -- Jeff Elorriaga scored 22 points to lead Boise State over Texas-Arlington 64-46 on Wednesday night, extending the Broncos winning streak to five games. Elorriaga, who was 6 of 9 from 3-point range, also led the Broncos (11-2) with nine rebounds. Anthony Drmic added 10 points. Boise State led 26-18 at halftime. The Broncos shot 48.9 percent (22 of 45) from the field for the game. The Mavericks (6-5) shot just 33 percent (16 of 48). Senior forwards Brandon Edwards and Karol Gruszecki led the Mavericks with nine points apiece. Edwards also had 10 rebounds. Boise State will host Walla Walla on Saturday. The Mavericks will play Louisiana Tech on Saturday.
